HEADWORD: Anacardiaceous
<hw>An`a*car"di*a"ceous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Belonging to, or resembling, a family, or order,
of plants of which the cashew tree is the type, and the species of sumac
are well known examples.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

